1447
00:53:59,861 --> 00:54:01,446
Wow. They smell so good by the way.

1448
00:54:01,529 --> 00:54:02,989
Look at this, wow.

1449
00:54:03,490 --> 00:54:05,033
These are all big ones.

1450
00:54:05,617 --> 00:54:06,660
This one's huge.

1451
00:54:06,743 --> 00:54:08,078
- That's a big one.
- I got a big one.

1452
00:54:08,161 --> 00:54:09,704
- Look at this one.
- Over here.

1453
00:54:09,788 --> 00:54:11,081
- There are a lot of them.
- Check this out.

1454
00:54:11,164 --> 00:54:13,583
It's like a gold mine.

1455
00:54:14,167 --> 00:54:16,294
- Come on, Team Sweet Potato.
- Come on.

1456
00:54:16,378 --> 00:54:18,004
Sweet potato!

1457
00:54:18,505 --> 00:54:20,632
There are so many of them.

1458
00:54:21,424 --> 00:54:22,676
There are so many of them.

1459
00:54:23,468 --> 00:54:25,512
It hasn't been this quiet in a while.

1460
00:54:25,595 --> 00:54:27,681
Five more minutes and then we get to work.

1461
00:54:28,348 --> 00:54:29,474
What are we doing first?

1462
00:54:30,141 --> 00:54:32,018
The toilet's clogged
in the women's bathroom.

1463
00:54:32,102 --> 00:54:34,479
Well, luckily, we have a plunger.

1464
00:54:34,562 --> 00:54:35,855
- I'll handle it.
- You stick it in

1465
00:54:35,939 --> 00:54:37,565
and give it a few good plunges, yeah?

1466
00:54:37,649 --> 00:54:41,069
So we'll do a big cleanup
and unclog the toilet.

1467
00:54:41,152 --> 00:54:42,737
That's it.

1468
00:54:42,821 --> 00:54:45,115
Let's go and… Oh, right. Hang on.

1469
00:54:45,198 --> 00:54:46,491
Campfire prep.

1470
00:54:46,992 --> 00:54:48,910
- Sorry?
- The campfire.

1471
00:54:48,994 --> 00:54:51,621
- We're prepping the campfire?
- We need to chop some wood.

1472
00:54:51,705 --> 00:54:53,123
B&B MAINTENANCE TO-DO LIST

1473
00:54:53,206 --> 00:54:56,001
We need to decide
where to have the campfire.

1474
00:54:56,084 --> 00:54:58,003
This would be a good spot,
except the ground's too muddy.

1475
00:54:58,086 --> 00:54:59,212
Yeah, it's too muddy.

1476
00:54:59,296 --> 00:55:02,382
FROM LAST NIGHT UNTIL
THIS MORNING, IT KEPT RAINING

1477
00:55:03,341 --> 00:55:06,553
AND LEFT PUDDLES
ALL OVER THE FIELD

1478
00:55:07,137 --> 00:55:08,888
I saw some tools in there,

1479
00:55:08,972 --> 00:55:11,474
so we should use those to scoop out
as much water as we can

1480
00:55:11,558 --> 00:55:13,977
and clear up a big space.

1481
00:55:14,060 --> 00:55:16,646
- Yeah, okay.
- And our campfire can be there.

1482
00:55:16,730 --> 00:55:18,565
We should do this first, right?

1483
00:55:18,648 --> 00:55:19,858
CLEARING PUDDLES

1484
00:55:20,859 --> 00:55:22,569
THE DOOR BROTHERS
PICK UP THE TOOLS

1485
00:55:22,652 --> 00:55:24,321
- …for the water.
- Mmm.

1486
00:55:24,821 --> 00:55:26,531
Should we grab the broom too?

1487
00:55:26,614 --> 00:55:28,033
- The broom?
- Yeah.

1488
00:55:29,034 --> 00:55:30,952
WHEN THE YOUNGER ONE PICKS UP
WHAT THE OLDER ONE SAYS

1489
00:55:33,038 --> 00:55:37,125
THE OLDER ONE QUICKLY
HAULS AWAY THE CART

1490
00:55:37,709 --> 00:55:39,210
CHIEF YU'S GEARED UP TOO

1491
00:55:39,294 --> 00:55:40,837
Let's do this one, Kwang-soo.

1492
00:55:42,464 --> 00:55:43,465
Okay.

1493
00:55:44,299 --> 00:55:45,842
Wow. There's a lot of water.

1494
00:55:45,925 --> 00:55:47,469
- Yeah, that's a lot.
- It keeps filling back up.

1495
00:55:48,386 --> 00:55:50,096
It's like instant coffee.

1496
00:55:50,180 --> 00:55:52,098
A MASSIVE AMOUNT
OF INSTANT COFFEE

1497
00:55:52,182 --> 00:55:53,183
Good work.

1498
00:55:53,266 --> 00:55:55,477
ONCE MOST OF THE WATER'S OUT,
POUR IN SAND

1499
00:55:55,560 --> 00:55:57,645
That's my staff. They're good workers.

1500
00:55:57,729 --> 00:55:59,856
PERFECT TEAMWORK

1501
00:56:00,398 --> 00:56:01,691
That's right.

1502
00:56:01,775 --> 00:56:02,942
This isn't easy.

1503
00:56:03,026 --> 00:56:04,778
- Seriously.
- Yeah. Gonna be tough.

1504
00:56:05,653 --> 00:56:06,738
We need to add more here.

1505
00:56:07,405 --> 00:56:08,698
Do we have any more sand?

1506
00:56:08,782 --> 00:56:10,241
- There's more.
- Yeah, there's more.

1507
00:56:10,325 --> 00:56:11,326
I'll go get it.

1508
00:56:19,626 --> 00:56:21,836
ALL THE SAND FROM STORAGE

1509
00:56:21,920 --> 00:56:24,214
LOADED UP

1510
00:56:26,216 --> 00:56:28,259
THE HYUNGS AND YE-EUN
CONTINUE SCOOPING

1511
00:56:30,553 --> 00:56:32,931
TRANSPORTING 100 KG BY HIMSELF

1512
00:56:33,515 --> 00:56:34,516
HURRY, BRING US THE SAND

1513
00:56:34,599 --> 00:56:36,559
- There's so much water.
- Woo-seok, you brought a lot.

1514
00:56:36,643 --> 00:56:38,311
- I just brought all of it.
- What do you mean?

1515
00:56:38,395 --> 00:56:40,188
Wow, Woo-seok. You're so strong.

1516
00:56:41,189 --> 00:56:42,690
How did you bring all this by yourself?

1517
00:56:42,774 --> 00:56:44,984
Whoa, this is pretty heavy.

1518
00:56:45,068 --> 00:56:47,695
- We should pour it here too.
- Okay, where?

1519
00:56:47,779 --> 00:56:49,614
Here.

1520
00:56:49,697 --> 00:56:50,865
I'll bring this over to you.

1521
00:56:50,949 --> 00:56:52,409
- Okay.
- Good.

1522
00:56:53,201 --> 00:56:54,702
POUR IT IN

1523
00:56:55,870 --> 00:56:57,664
POUR SOME MORE

1524
00:56:58,832 --> 00:57:01,042
POUR IT ALL IN

1525
00:57:02,001 --> 00:57:04,003
SPREAD IT OUT

1526
00:57:06,214 --> 00:57:09,050
Wow, this is like pouring concrete.

1527
00:57:10,301 --> 00:57:13,346
SMOOTH IT OUT
LIKE YOU'RE FINISHING CONCRETE

1528
00:57:14,055 --> 00:57:15,932
HAUL SAND AGAIN

1529
00:57:16,558 --> 00:57:19,519
Bailing water out of the field
really shook me mentally.

1530
00:57:19,602 --> 00:57:22,355
That's something I used to do
in the military.

1531
00:57:22,439 --> 00:57:24,107
I couldn't help but wonder

1532
00:57:24,190 --> 00:57:25,942
"What am I doing right now?"

1533
00:57:27,235 --> 00:57:30,572
YOU'RE RUNNING A B&B

1534
00:57:31,656 --> 00:57:33,741
Why is there so much water underneath?

1535
00:57:35,076 --> 00:57:37,328
HERE

1536
00:57:37,412 --> 00:57:38,621
THERE

1537
00:57:41,749 --> 00:57:42,792
There's no more sand.

1538
00:57:42,876 --> 00:57:43,877
DOWN TO THE LAST SACK

1539
00:57:45,253 --> 00:57:47,297
SHAKING OUT EVERY LAST BIT

1540
00:57:54,137 --> 00:57:55,305
THE PUDDLES ARE MOSTLY GONE

1541
00:57:55,388 --> 00:57:56,431
There.

1542
00:57:56,514 --> 00:57:57,932
The fire will go out to here.

1543
00:57:58,433 --> 00:57:59,809
Looks good.

1544
00:57:59,893 --> 00:58:01,686
- Done.
- Good, good.

1545
00:58:01,769 --> 00:58:04,564
- We did the best we could.
- I think it'll be fine.

1546
00:58:05,064 --> 00:58:06,065
Let's go.

1547
00:58:06,149 --> 00:58:07,400
Man, I'm sweating.

1548
00:58:08,359 --> 00:58:09,569
I was getting dizzy.

1549
00:58:10,987 --> 00:58:13,656
Hyung, your face looks slimmer
than when we first got here.

1550
00:58:14,449 --> 00:58:15,700
LOOKING GAUNT

1551
00:58:16,576 --> 00:58:19,204
- Should we put it in here?
- Let's load up some wood.

1552
00:58:19,287 --> 00:58:20,914
NEXT, LOADING UP THE FIREWOOD

1553
00:58:21,873 --> 00:58:24,959
Hang on,
do people who run B&Bs usually do this?

1554
00:58:26,544 --> 00:58:28,671
Is this actually part of the job?

1555
00:58:28,755 --> 00:58:30,757
The guests have already done
more than their fair share.

1556
00:58:30,840 --> 00:58:33,676
- I know. I mean, I do appreciate that.
- You should.

1557
00:58:33,760 --> 00:58:35,720
- You can always go home.
- No, that's not what I meant.

1558
00:58:35,803 --> 00:58:36,804
Thought so.

1559
00:58:37,430 --> 00:58:39,432
So, we're going to use this as fuel.

1560
00:58:39,516 --> 00:58:40,558
CHOPPING WOOD FOR KINDLING

1561
00:58:41,142 --> 00:58:42,602
I'm good at chopping wood.

1562
00:58:44,187 --> 00:58:45,396
Have you ever done this?

1563
00:58:45,480 --> 00:58:47,440
- Well, I've used an ax…
- But you've done it, right?

1564
00:58:47,524 --> 00:58:48,942
…but it was with a hammer.

1565
00:58:49,651 --> 00:58:50,652
Whoa!

1566
00:58:52,320 --> 00:58:53,947
NOT EVEN CLOSE

1567
00:58:54,822 --> 00:58:56,366
I should have hit it harder.

1568
00:58:56,449 --> 00:58:57,784
That surprised me.

1569
00:58:59,494 --> 00:59:00,912
WOBBLING

1570
00:59:00,995 --> 00:59:03,540
- I knew it. That's his best.
- Put it back.

1571
00:59:03,623 --> 00:59:05,416
I was being careful because of you guys.

1572
00:59:05,500 --> 00:59:06,918
SPITTING

1573
00:59:07,001 --> 00:59:08,002
It was a good start.

1574
00:59:08,503 --> 00:59:09,963
Gotta split it with the grain.

1575
00:59:11,673 --> 00:59:12,840
WITH THE GRAIN

1576
00:59:14,509 --> 00:59:15,510
UH…

1577
00:59:16,094 --> 00:59:17,095
- Hyung…
- Again.

1578
00:59:17,178 --> 00:59:18,346
This is a tough one.

1579
00:59:20,223 --> 00:59:21,224
SLIP

1580
00:59:22,642 --> 00:59:24,018
- Hyung…
- Don't stop me!

1581
00:59:24,727 --> 00:59:25,853
HYUNG…

1582
00:59:25,937 --> 00:59:27,146
- Stop, stop.
- Let me go!

1583
00:59:27,230 --> 00:59:28,356
No, stop.

1584
00:59:28,439 --> 00:59:29,440
EGO BRUISED

1585
00:59:29,524 --> 00:59:31,818
- You have to twist it out.
- I think it's because it's damp.

1586
00:59:31,901 --> 00:59:32,902
Right.

1587
00:59:32,986 --> 00:59:35,530
KWANG-SOO TRIES

1588
00:59:36,531 --> 00:59:37,949
CRACK

1589
00:59:38,032 --> 00:59:39,033
Oh!

1590
00:59:40,118 --> 00:59:41,160
Oh!

1591
00:59:42,203 --> 00:59:43,204
HACKING AWAY NONSTOP

1592
00:59:43,288 --> 00:59:45,123
- Whoa!
- Nice. Great swing.

1593
00:59:45,206 --> 00:59:47,292
I WILL SPLIT IT

1594
00:59:47,959 --> 00:59:49,752
- Whoa.
- Nice.

1595
00:59:52,338 --> 00:59:53,339
Great!

1596
00:59:54,048 --> 00:59:55,883
- Go, Kwang-soo!
- Good job.

1597
01:00:00,972 --> 01:00:02,390
Nicely done.

1598
01:00:02,473 --> 01:00:03,558
All right, Woo-seok. You try.

1599
01:00:03,641 --> 01:00:05,101
- So I just do it?
- Yeah.

1600
01:00:10,857 --> 01:00:11,899
A base hit.

1601
01:00:11,983 --> 01:00:13,151
A BASE HIT(?)

1602
01:00:13,234 --> 01:00:14,611
Woo-seok just hurt his hand.

1603
01:00:14,694 --> 01:00:16,237
- You okay there?
- He hurt his hand.

1604
01:00:16,321 --> 01:00:18,448
No, let me try again.
It's just my first time.

1605
01:00:18,531 --> 01:00:19,824
All right. This is hard, you know.

1606
01:00:19,907 --> 01:00:21,200
SECOND TRY

1607
01:00:21,284 --> 01:00:22,952
Like this? Bam.

1608
01:00:27,582 --> 01:00:28,583
HITTING THE GROUND

1609
01:00:28,666 --> 01:00:29,959
- Woo-seok.
- Step aside.

1610
01:00:30,043 --> 01:00:32,670
No, wait.
My beanie fell down over my eyes.

1611
01:00:32,754 --> 01:00:34,339
YOUR BEANIE?

1612
01:00:34,422 --> 01:00:36,007
- One more time.
- All right, last try.

1613
01:00:36,591 --> 01:00:38,051
THIRD TRY

1614
01:00:38,134 --> 01:00:39,135
Good.

1615
01:00:40,595 --> 01:00:41,596
That's good.

1616
01:00:41,679 --> 01:00:43,014
Good.

1617
01:00:43,097 --> 01:00:44,182
My beanie keeps coming down.

1618
01:00:44,265 --> 01:00:45,266
ARE YOU SURE IT'S THE BEANIE?

1619
01:00:45,350 --> 01:00:47,060
- That was really…
- No, it's my beanie.

1620
01:00:47,560 --> 01:00:48,853
Hey, they're coming back.

1621
01:00:48,936 --> 01:00:51,898
We really need to to get
some of the wood chopped before then.

1622
01:00:52,690 --> 01:00:53,733
This will do it.

1623
01:00:54,942 --> 01:00:57,445
Right down the middle. Oh!

1624
01:00:59,030 --> 01:01:00,156
Oh, good one.

1625
01:01:00,239 --> 01:01:01,240
A CLEAN SPLIT

1626
01:01:02,283 --> 01:01:03,868
- Oh, good one. Nicely done.
- Okay, good.

1627
01:01:03,951 --> 01:01:04,952
You got the hang of it.

1628
01:01:05,536 --> 01:01:06,537
ONCE HE GOT THE HANG OF IT

1629
01:01:06,621 --> 01:01:07,705
Nice one.

1630
01:01:08,665 --> 01:01:09,749
Oh!

1631
01:01:10,583 --> 01:01:11,584
- There.
- Good job.

1632
01:01:11,668 --> 01:01:12,835
CLEAN

1633
01:01:13,878 --> 01:01:15,505
SPLIT

1634
01:01:16,089 --> 01:01:17,465
SPLIT AGAIN

1635
01:01:17,548 --> 01:01:18,925
We got a great shot of that.

1636
01:01:19,008 --> 01:01:20,593
GOT A GOOD SHOT

1637
01:01:20,677 --> 01:01:21,928
Let's stack them up over here.

1638
01:01:22,011 --> 01:01:23,346
NEXT, STACKING FIREWOOD

1639
01:01:23,429 --> 01:01:26,307
- Stack them up in a box shape.
- Like a hashtag?

1640
01:01:27,100 --> 01:01:28,226
Put it here.

1641
01:01:28,309 --> 01:01:30,603
- Put the thin ones in here.
- Oh, like that.

1642
01:01:30,687 --> 01:01:31,896
TUCK THIN PIECES INTO THE STACK

1643
01:01:31,979 --> 01:01:33,272
Stack a few more.

1644
01:01:33,356 --> 01:01:35,525
- Isn't that too tall?
- Okay, that's good.

1645
01:01:36,025 --> 01:01:38,236
STACK THEM UP HIGH

1646
01:01:38,820 --> 01:01:41,364
- It'll be like fireworks.
- It's like summer camp.

1647
01:01:42,323 --> 01:01:44,075
Yu Jae-seok's B&B Rules!

1648
01:01:46,035 --> 01:01:47,036
Good job, guys.

1649
01:01:47,120 --> 01:01:49,038
Ah, this feels good.

1650
01:01:49,539 --> 01:01:52,041
All right, now.
Let's clean up before they come back.

1651
01:01:52,542 --> 01:01:54,460
NO TIME TO REST

1652
01:01:54,544 --> 01:01:57,547
I think they'll be back
in about two hours.

1653
01:01:57,630 --> 01:02:00,466
Wait, hyung, we need to prep
the barbecue stuff too.

1654
01:02:00,550 --> 01:02:02,218
We need to do that too.

1655
01:02:02,927 --> 01:02:05,138
We should get the charcoal ready first.

1656
01:02:05,221 --> 01:02:06,472
Should I go grab it?

1657
01:02:07,056 --> 01:02:09,892
Ugh, Ye-eun, this is so exhausting.
The work never ends.

1658
01:02:12,145 --> 01:02:13,855
SETTING UP THE BBQ GEAR

1659
01:02:13,938 --> 01:02:15,356
- Is this enough?
- Yeah.

1660
01:02:15,440 --> 01:02:16,566
Three should be good.

1661
01:02:16,649 --> 01:02:19,986
- You know, I'll be honest…
- Yeah?

1662
01:02:20,069 --> 01:02:21,529
I don't really like barbecues.

1663
01:02:22,196 --> 01:02:23,656
BUZZKILL

1664
01:02:23,740 --> 01:02:25,950
Some people are good at grilling meat.

1665
01:02:26,033 --> 01:02:27,910
- I'm good at grilling. Yeah.
- Oh, really?

1666
01:02:28,494 --> 01:02:30,121
BBQ GEAR SETUP COMPLETE

1667
01:02:30,204 --> 01:02:31,289
GYMNASIUM CLEANUP

1668
01:02:31,372 --> 01:02:32,790
Should we start with vacuuming?

1669
01:02:33,875 --> 01:02:36,419
DRAGGING THEIR TIRED BODIES
TO GET THE VACUUM

1670
01:02:36,502 --> 01:02:38,337
Here we are.

1671
01:02:38,421 --> 01:02:40,006
Oh, the mop.

1672
01:02:40,590 --> 01:02:41,758
Ever do this in school, Ye-eun?

1673
01:02:41,841 --> 01:02:43,676
- Oh, yeah, all the time.
- Yeah?

1674
01:02:43,760 --> 01:02:47,930
REMEMBERING HIS SCHOOL DAYS,
HE WORKS LIKE A PRO

1675
01:02:49,140 --> 01:02:50,141
- Shake all the water out.
- Okay.

1676
01:02:50,224 --> 01:02:51,225
MANUAL WATER SHAKE-OUT

1677
01:02:51,309 --> 01:02:52,310
That'll do.

1678
01:02:52,393 --> 01:02:55,021
THE MOP SQUAD'S ON THE MOVE

1679
01:02:55,104 --> 01:02:58,357
THE VACUUM SQUAD'S
ON THE MOVE TOO

1680
01:03:01,569 --> 01:03:03,154
STRAIGHTENING HIS HAT,
LOOKING DETERMINED

1681
01:03:03,821 --> 01:03:05,281
OFF TO HUNT DOWN DUST

1682
01:03:06,491 --> 01:03:07,784
EVERY NOOK AND CRANNY

1683
01:03:10,953 --> 01:03:12,747
There's some dust clumped up.

1684
01:03:13,748 --> 01:03:16,542
ONCE THE VACUUM SQUAD
WIPES OUT THE DUST

1685
01:03:17,543 --> 01:03:20,505
WITHOUT A SINGLE SPECK
LEFT BEHIND

1686
01:03:21,088 --> 01:03:23,382
IN COMES THE MOP SQUAD

1687
01:03:23,966 --> 01:03:26,844
MOPPING IN A LONG, STRAIGHT LINE

1688
01:03:31,849 --> 01:03:33,226
FREE-SPIRITED TYPE

1689
01:03:35,937 --> 01:03:37,688
- Ye-eun.
- Yeah?

1690
01:03:38,731 --> 01:03:39,941
DO IT IN A STRAIGHT LINE

1691
01:03:41,484 --> 01:03:42,652
GOT IT?

1692
01:03:42,735 --> 01:03:44,278
Okay.

1693
01:03:44,821 --> 01:03:45,988
That's it. Mop up all the dust.

1694
01:03:46,072 --> 01:03:47,073
LONG, STRAIGHT LINE

1695
01:03:47,156 --> 01:03:49,826
The dust in an indoor space like this…

1696
01:03:49,909 --> 01:03:50,910
MOPPING BACK-AND-FORTH

1697
01:03:50,993 --> 01:03:52,578
